<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Editing an item's properties</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Setting up an imposition style</p>
<p class="text">To set up a imposition style, go to Items and click on Imposition...
  in the submenu. Then click &quot;Add new imposition...&quot; next to the imposition menu
  and click the Save button. Modify the settings
  to the desired
  imposition layout.</p>
<p class="text">An imposition style is used to determine the imposition layout
  for ordered items. Each item must have an imposition style selected before
  it will show up in the list of ordered items on the Impose screen.</p>
</body>
</html>
